deportation. That's after a
federal appeals court panel

01:50.143 --> 01:55.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ruled against the president's
executive orders to do just
that. Monday's ruling upheld an

01:55.015 --> 01:59.619 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
injunction issued by a
federal judge in Texas.

01:59.619 --> 02:03.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, White House spokesman
Josh Earnest said the
administration is determined to
continue

02:03.256 --> 02:05.192 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the fight.

02:05.192 --> 02:07.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSH EARNEST, White House Press
Secretary: We're quite
disappointed in the decision
that

02:07.527 --> 02:12.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was rendered by the Fifth
Circuit, but it did not in any
way diminish the confidence

02:12.866 --> 02:17.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that we have in the power of our
legal argument. And we're
looking forward to having an
opportunity

02:17.037 --> 02:20.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
making that argument again
before the Supreme Court.

02:20.207 --> 02:24.644 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In all, 26 states
have challenged the president's
actions on immigration, saying

02:24.644 --> 02:28.248 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
they illegally
circumvent Congress.

02:28.248 --> 02:32.886 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: The Senate
overwhelmingly passed a defense
bill today that includes a ban
on

02:32.886 --> 02:38.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
