to the United States. It's the
latest obstacle to President

02:38.825 --> 02:44.598 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obama's pledge to close the
detention facility before he
leaves office. Still, the White

02:44.598 --> 02:49.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
House said he will sign the $600
billion measure because of other
important provisions.

02:49.803 --> 02:56.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The worst El Nino
weather pattern in decades could
threaten 11 million children

02:56.176 --> 03:01.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Africa with hunger, disease
and drought. The United Nations
Children's Fund, UNICEF,

03:01.648 --> 03:04.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
issued that warning today.

03:04.718 --> 03:09.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a statement, it said: "The
consequences could ripple
through generations, unless
affected

03:09.122 --> 03:12.426 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
communities receive support."

03:12.426 --> 03:18.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The weather pattern has already
caused severe drought in
Ethiopia and flooding in
Somalia.

03:18.331 --> 03:24.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Myanmar, official
results from Sunday's elections
kept trickling in today,

03:24.738 --> 03:29.042 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as the opposition claimed a
landslide win. The country's
constitution bars opposition

03:29.042 --> 03:33.280 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
leader Aung San Suu Kyi
from becoming president.

03:33.280 --> 03:38.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
