renewable energy. They have
issued reports, one as recently

14:11.284 --> 14:17.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as last year in response to
shareholder requests and public
requests, estimating that
switching

14:17.757 --> 14:23.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over to renewables by the end of
this century would raise energy
costs, to the point that

14:23.429 --> 14:28.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they would cost -- they would be
44 percent of the median income
of an American family.

14:28.101 --> 14:32.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We want to see how they arrived
at that conclusion, which we
believe to be vastly overstated.

14:32.405 --> 14:39.212 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you draw a
line between ExxonMobil doing
research and talking openly

14:39.212 --> 14:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about the debate out there about
what is known about climate
change, and on the other hand

14:44.417 --> 14:48.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
