41:17.041 --> 41:35.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: A new initiative
designed to make soccer safer
for young players was just
announced

41:35.927 --> 41:41.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the U.S. Soccer Federation.
The new rule would set limits on
how much players could

41:41.265 --> 41:44.802 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
use their heads to physically
hit the ball. The hope is that
it would reduce the number

41:44.802 --> 41:47.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of concussions and
head injuries.

41:47.739 --> 41:51.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
William Brangham has more on the
changes and the emerging science
behind them.

41:51.943 --> 41:55.880 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Today, soccer
is one of the leading causes of
concussions for young

41:55.880 --> 42:00.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
athletes in the U.S. It's not as
high as the concussion rate for
football, but it's close.

42:00.485 --> 42:03.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tens of thousands of kids get
concussions playing soccer every
year, and heading the

42:03.454 --> 42:06.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ball is considered
a main culprit.

42:06.758 --> 42:10.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Under U.S. soccer's new rules,
kids under the age of 10 won't
be heading the ball at

42:10.962 --> 42:15.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all. Kids aged 11-13 will head
the ball much less in practice.
And there will be new rules

42:15.833 --> 42:21.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on injury substitutions during
games. Players 14 and up will
continue heading as always.

42:21.906 --> 42:25.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These new rules will resolve a
lawsuit brought last year
against U.S. soccer and others
by

42:25.743 --> 42:30.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a group of parents in California
who argued the groups weren't
doing enough to protect

42:30.148 --> 42:34.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
kids from head injuries. Last
year, we reported on the rising
concern over concussions in

42:34.419 --> 42:38.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
soccer and the push to limit
heading for young players.

42:38.689 --> 42:43.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back then, I talked with one of
the leading scientists in the
field, Dr. Robert Cantu.

42:43.261 --> 42:47.899 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He's a neurosurgeon and
co-directs a brain study center
at Boston University. Cantu
acknowledged

42:47.899 --> 42:51.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the science connecting
soccer and brain injury was
limited. He's in fact called for

42:51.369 --> 42:54.372 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
much more research to be done.

42:54.372 --> 42:57.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, even so, he's argued that
it's better to be safe and not
allow young kids to repeatedly

42:57.875 --> 43:00.111 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
head the ball.

43:00.111 --> 43:03.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. ROBERT CANTU, Concussion
Legacy Foundation: If you took
heading out of soccer, it
wouldn't

43:03.414 --> 43:07.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be behind football in the
incidence of concussion. It
wouldn't even be in the
high-risk group.

43:07.518 --> 43:10.855 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It would be in a low-risk group.

43:10.855 --> 43:14.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Cantu told me
that heading the ball, as well
as the collisions and hard

43:14.258 --> 43:18.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
falls to the ground they often
cause, are problematic for kids,
because, unlike adult

43:18.763 --> 43:21.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
brains, kids' brains
are still developing.

43:21.833 --> 43:27.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ROBERT CANTU: The young
brain is largely not myelinated.
Myelin is the coating of nerve

43:27.638 --> 43:32.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fibers that connect nerve cells.
Similar to coating on a
telephone wire, it helps
transmission

43:32.410 --> 43:35.646 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but it also gives strength.

43:35.646 --> 43:39.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so when you violently shake
the young brain, you have a much
greater chance to disrupt

43:39.784 --> 43:44.889 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
nerve fibers and their
connections than you do an adult
brain.

43:44.889 --> 43:49.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Cantu says a
kids head also sits on a much
less developed neck and torso

43:49.327 --> 43:52.830 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than an adult's does, so the
same blow might cause more
shaking to a kid's head than it

43:52.830 --> 43:54.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
would to a grownup's.

43:54.966 --> 43:59.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ROBERT CANTU: So, you've got
a bobblehead doll effect with
our youngsters, so that the

43:59.904 --> 44:04.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
very minimal impact is now going
to set their brain in much more
motion than it would in

44:04.842 --> 44:07.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
an adult brain with
a strong neck.

44:07.545 --> 44:11.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Cantu says
strengthening a kid's neck
muscles can help, but those
soccer

44:11.916 --> 44:15.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
helmets and headgear that you
see on the market don't really
offer much protection, so he

44:15.253 --> 44:18.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
says there's only one
thing left to do.

44:18.055 --> 44:23.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DR. ROBERT CANTU: Take the most
injurious activity for head
injury out of it, but let

44:23.694 --> 44:27.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the rest of the sport go on. And
that's playing soccer without
heading.

44:27.231 --> 44:31.602 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: You can watch
the full report on our Web site,
PBS.org/NewsHour. You can

44:31.602 --> 44:37.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also read a longer interview
with Dr. Cantu about concussions
in youth sports.

44:37.909 --> 44:49.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: The story of
a screenwriter comes to the
screen.

44:49.654 --> 44:53.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His name was Dalton Trumbo. And
his life and work were
intertwined with a controversial

44:53.357 --> 44:56.460 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
period of film history.

44:56.460 --> 45:00.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has a look at
Trumbo for the "NewsHour" at the
Movies.

45:00.331 --> 45:05.036 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Dalton Trumbo was
one of the most successful
Hollywood screenwriters of

45:05.036 --> 45:13.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his generation. He was also an
activist in labor and other
causes who joined the Communist

45:13.611 --> 45:16.881 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Party in the 1940s.

45:16.881 --> 45:22.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As the Cold War consumed the
nation, Trumbo gained a new kind
of fame, as a member of

45:22.286 --> 45:27.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the so-called Hollywood 10,
writers, actors and others who
were brought before the
Congressional

45:27.124 --> 45:35.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
House on Un-American Activities
Consulate and blacklisted by the
major studios.

45:35.700 --> 45:40.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trumbo would spend almost a year
in prison, then, for nearly a
decade, could only work

45:40.838 --> 45:45.476 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
using a pseudonym. One
screenplay during that time
written under the name Robert
Rich for

45:45.476 --> 45:50.014 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the film "The Brave Ones"
even earned an Oscar.

45:50.014 --> 45:53.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Only in 1960, with his scripts
for the blockbuster films
"Spartacus" and "Exodus," was
Trumbo

45:53.718 --> 45:57.188 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
able to work openly again.

45:57.188 --> 46:01.726 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bryan Cranston, who plays Trumbo
in the new film, is best known
for his role as Walter

46:01.726 --> 46:06.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
White in the TV drama "Breaking
Bad." He and Trumbo director Jay
Roach joined me to speak

46:06.564 --> 46:09.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about the film and the
man it was based on.

46:09.400 --> 46:12.169 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I asked Cranston what
attracted him to the script.

46:12.169 --> 46:16.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON, Actor: And this
was an amazing story about the
jeopardy of the First Amendment

46:16.407 --> 46:24.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rights to an industry, the
Hollywood film industry, that
wasn't used to being scrutinized

46:24.015 --> 46:26.917 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like that.

46:26.917 --> 46:34.058 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the ripple effect that the
eventual blacklist had on that
community was profound. And the

46:34.058 --> 46:41.465 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
character himself of Dalton
Trumbo was just bigger than
life, dramatic, flamboyant. He

46:41.465 --> 46:47.772 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was a contrarian. He could be
very irascible. He was a pretty
hard drinker and a chain smoker.

46:47.772 --> 46:49.707 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes, constantly
throughout the film.

46:49.707 --> 46:51.876 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Constantly.

46:51.876 --> 46:56.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How did you fill
in -- you have to take this
individual, right, but fill

46:56.480 --> 46:59.350 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it in to a kind of history
that is real history.

46:59.350 --> 47:00.317 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JAY ROACH, Director,
"Trumbo": yes.

47:00.317 --> 47:02.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How much did you
know? How much did you fill in?

47:02.853 --> 47:08.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAY ROACH: It was more about
extracting from this incredibly
complex story, a 13-year story,

47:08.693 --> 47:11.829 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to distill it down to something
that was accessible.

47:11.829 --> 47:16.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that really -- I have to
credit our great screenwriter
who told the story about a
screenwriter.

47:16.367 --> 47:23.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
John McNamara had -- had done a
few things to make it more sort
of relatable and manageable

47:23.641 --> 47:27.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
by doing a couple
composite characters.

47:27.311 --> 47:32.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Louis C.K. plays a guy who
represents two of three of the
blacklisted writers. And there

47:32.750 --> 47:37.154 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are a few choices like that that
just made it a story you could
tell in two hours.

47:37.154 --> 47:39.523 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You have to
dramatize it. Do you also -- you
also have responsibility to

47:39.523 --> 47:40.958 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the history.

47:40.958 --> 47:44.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAY ROACH: Of course, and -- but
the main responsibility, I
think, is to get to the

47:44.695 --> 47:48.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
essence of what mattered to
these people and to the battle
itself, who they were up
against,

47:48.866 --> 47:52.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
how the obstacles related,
and how they overcame them.

47:52.536 --> 47:56.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You are always going to --
there's never been a -- quote,
unquote -- "historical film"
that

47:56.373 --> 48:03.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
didn't have to vary from the
beat-by-beat reality of it. But
as long as you stay true

48:03.848 --> 48:08.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the essence of what the
people are up to, I think it's
-- I think it becomes very
authentic.

48:08.285 --> 48:13.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we did a tremendous amount
of research. We spoke to the
daughters of Trumbo. We spoke

48:13.390 --> 48:18.162 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Kirk Douglas. We read every
possible book and saw every
possible bit of film or radio

48:18.162 --> 48:20.464 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
that we -- and
listened to radio.

48:20.464 --> 48:24.535 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Very complicated
character, right, I mean, larger
than life in many ways,

48:24.535 --> 48:29.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
big in many ways, committed, and
yet loving a kind of life,
right?

48:29.473 --> 48:34.578 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BRYAN CRANSTON: He was a
very idiosyncratic man.

48:34.578 --> 48:41.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was a member of the American
Communist Party. He was very
compassionate about workers'

48:41.552 --> 48:48.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rights. He led a lot of strikes
when he was young, especially
for himself, in a bakery

48:48.826 --> 48:57.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when he was very young. And he
was very much a pro-worker
individual.

48:57.301 --> 49:04.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But he also loved being a
wealthy man. He was the highest
paid screenwriter in the '40s,

49:04.308 --> 49:07.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that tantamount to saying
the highest paid writer in the
world. And he loved that

49:07.812 --> 49:09.246 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
idea.

49:09.246 --> 49:11.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Do you enjoy the
contradiction of that, I mean,
as an actor?

49:11.549 --> 49:12.616 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Oh, as an
actor, it's juicy, yes.

49:12.616 --> 49:14.351 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

49:14.351 --> 49:18.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Any time -- any
time someone makes an emphatic
statement and then goes

49:18.455 --> 49:23.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
against it, it's like -- it's
quite fun to play both sides of
those things.

49:23.627 --> 49:28.032 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let's -- I want
the play one scene. This is you
as Dalton Trumbo and Louis

49:28.032 --> 49:31.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
C.K., who you just mentioned,
talking about this very thing.
Right?

49:31.202 --> 49:33.037 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's watch that.

49:33.037 --> 49:36.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LOUIS C.K., Actor: No, you know
what it is? I don't trust you.

49:36.207 --> 49:39.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Well, I would
say go on, but I'm afraid you
will.

49:39.310 --> 49:42.580 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOUIS C.K.: Look, I know what I
am. OK? I want this whole
country to be different top

49:42.580 --> 49:46.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to bottom. If I get what I want,
nobody gets their own lake.

49:46.283 --> 49:49.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Well, that would
be a very dull life, don't you
think?

49:49.119 --> 49:53.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOUIS C.K.: Yes, for you, not
for the guys who built this. If
I'm wrong, tell me, but

49:53.357 --> 49:57.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ever since I know you, you talk
like a radical, but you live
like a rich guy.

49:57.995 --> 50:01.365 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: That is true.

50:01.365 --> 50:03.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOUIS C.K.: Well, I don't know
that you're -- I don't think
you're willing to lose all

50:03.467 --> 50:06.971 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of this just to do
the right thing.

50:06.971 --> 50:13.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Well, I despise
martyrdom, and I won't fight for
a lost cause. So, you're

50:13.043 --> 50:17.114 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right. I'm not willing to lose
it all, certainly not them.

50:17.114 --> 50:24.622 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I am willing to risk it all.
That's where the radical and the
rich guy make a perfect

50:24.622 --> 50:29.760 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
combination. The radical may
fight with the purity of Jesus,
but the rich guy wins with

50:29.760 --> 50:30.761 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the cunning of Satan.

50:30.761 --> 50:32.463 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
LOUIS C.K.: Oh.

50:32.463 --> 50:34.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRYAN CRANSTON: What?

50:34.298 --> 50:37.768 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LOUIS C.K.: Just please shut up.

50:37.768 --> 50:42.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: This movie puts
-- well, puts the wider culture
under a microscope, right,

50:42.840 --> 50:46.243 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
under scrutiny, but also
Hollywood, which often doesn't
-- which doesn't come off
looking

50:46.243 --> 50:48.679 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
all that well, for
the most part.

50:48.679 --> 50:53.284 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAY ROACH: Hollywood turned
on itself in those days.

50:53.284 --> 50:59.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was a group of people,
Hedda Hopper, Walt Disney -- Ayn
Rand came and helped them

50:59.690 --> 51:07.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
out, some other directors, who
felt these writers were
polluting the minds of Americans

51:07.197 --> 51:11.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through mainstream Hollywood
movies, even though some of
them, like Trumbo, was a war

51:11.669 --> 51:15.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
correspondent, had written
"Thirty Seconds Over Tokyo" and
"A Guy Named Joe," very
patriotic,

51:15.906 --> 51:20.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
almost pro-war films, were
suddenly somehow seen as
traitors because they just had
different

51:20.778 --> 51:23.180 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
political views. That's
all it turned into.

51:23.180 --> 51:24.949 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: He
went to prison.

51:24.949 --> 51:27.151 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Mm-hmm.

51:27.151 --> 51:31.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He had to write
under a pseudonym. In the end,
he got the recognition. How do

51:31.155 --> 51:34.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you end up seeing him years
later? How do you look -- how do
you see him?

51:34.591 --> 51:38.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: You know, a lot
of people will look back and say
that he's a hero. There

51:38.562 --> 51:43.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are other people who will say,
he was no hero, he's a dirty red
commie or whatever.

51:43.233 --> 51:47.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I suppose the point of the
movie is that all opinions are
welcome. All opinions should

51:47.338 --> 51:50.274 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be heard.

51:50.274 --> 51:54.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't think Dalton Trumbo
would look at himself as a hero.
I think he would -- he

51:54.545 --> 52:00.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was practicing self-defense. He
didn't want this fight. The
fight came to him. He was

52:00.317 --> 52:08.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
subpoenaed to testify, under the
threat of incarceration, and
forced to let his First

52:08.826 --> 52:13.197 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
Amendment rights
go by the wayside.

52:13.197 --> 52:17.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he thought that -- that the
questions themselves were
un-American. And he kept asking:

52:17.701 --> 52:21.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Have I committed a crime? Do
you have any evidence that I
have committed some crime?

52:21.939 --> 52:24.174 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I would love to hear that."

52:24.174 --> 52:26.477 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
But that wasn't
part of the agenda.

52:26.477 --> 52:31.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAY ROACH: I thought, at least
as a person who didn't succumb
and who was victorious,

52:31.682 --> 52:36.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in that he kept writing until he
embarrassed the studios, wins
two Academy Awards, writes

52:36.954 --> 52:39.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Spartacus" and "Exodus," and
suddenly helps break the
blacklist.

52:39.857 --> 52:43.193 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, there is definitely, to me,
something heroic about that.

52:43.193 --> 52:45.496 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: And -- but along
with that was a tremendous
amount of pain and suffering.

52:45.496 --> 52:47.631 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

52:47.631 --> 52:52.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRYAN CRANSTON: People who not
only were not able to -- were --
taken away their personal

52:52.369 --> 52:57.741 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
freedoms, sent to jail, or taken
away their ability to pursue
their own career, which

52:57.741 --> 53:01.645 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
means you cannot
support your family.

53:01.645 --> 53:07.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It put tremendous pressure on
families. Marriages broke up.
Families dissipated, loss of
homes.

53:07.317 --> 53:12.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There were some suicides. Even
when you think of the ripple
effect and how far it goes,

53:12.489 --> 53:17.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the bullying of the children
going to school, who don't
understand what's going on, but

53:17.661 --> 53:19.229 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they're -- they know
that something is wrong.

53:19.229 --> 53:21.065 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right.

53:21.065 --> 53:23.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The film is "Trumbo."

53:23.167 --> 53:28.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Bryan Cranston and Jay Roach,
thank you both very much.

53:28.238 --> 53:30.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRYAN CRANSTON: Thanks.

53:30.741 --> 53:36.814 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAY ROACH: Thanks. Thanks a lot.

53:36.814 --> 53:43.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
